{
  "texts": [
    "The PR-AUC between PSSM-generated artificial VHH sequences and real camelid VHH sequences from the test set is 0.942.",
    "The VHH model can classify most of the diverse greater than 5% VHH sequences as native, with a performance at par to that observed on the test set.",
    "Also, 10.4% of diverse greater than 5% VHH sequences have a score below the nativeness characteristic threshold of 0.8, compared with 10.8% for the test VH sequences.",
    "To the best of our knowledge, AbNatiV is the first approach to quantify the nativeness of nanobodies.",
    "Therefore, to compare with a different model, we retrained the AbLSTM architecture, originally developed for human VH sequences, on our nanobody training set (Methods)."
  ]
}